social_posts.post_text: We met almost 11 yrs ago in Seoul. Someone took a pix at the airport lounge during those first trips. From then on you’d pick me up for my Korean shows and we’d race along highways in your fancy car and you’d blare my music. You would bring your posse and shoot pictures and tell magazines to put me on the cover and in exchange you would give them an interview even though you never did interviews. You met me first backstage and talked about the song ‘elephants’ and speak of how we understood each other’s sadness. You’d give me a kick in the butt talk when it was time to get back to work.  We would chainsmoke and drink coffee and talk about going to Africa. You called me Rei and spelled it with the ‘ei’. You brought us into your world and showed us your studios and new works and they are in every room of my house. I wrote you a song ‘I’ll meet you in Paris - JUNGMAN’s Theme’ and we dreamed of collaborations. You were my friend.  My dad loved you. Just this Christmas I framed a montage of pictures of you and him and when he opened it, he cried.  Years ago I had a psychic tell me I would meet someone that would be very important in my life - compared it to Georgia O’Keeffe and Alfred Stieglitz … I was most excited to show you my new songs because they are dark and deep and rich with sorrow and hope. So it’s fitting you pass at the end of this year on this rainy day of winter, warm and with beautiful barren trees surrounding me.  I hate that I hadn’t talked to you in a while. You are leaving me too soon and leaving the world to only have your beautiful works to go to.  Last night I happened to put your books near my piano because I am now finally getting back to work and I need your voice pushing me on. And this morning I woke from a dream with this red cardinal on winter branches up close to my face saying ‘hello’. I know now that was you.  I will not say goodbye my friend, but I will say see you again, my heart.  My plane leaves at 7am. I will see you soon. ❤️

It was a week of deep emotion and yet of such extraordinary love as well. We find family across the world and dear Jungman I thank you with such gratitude for continuing connection, inspiration and creation. Thank you to this family for welcoming us in during this time. The flow of grief, joy and magic - the strength and grace and depth of it all…forever love @74yc3 @african_seoul @eniwhere Anika and Neptune, my sisters and all surrounding him.  Thank you @padkapaw78 for nourishing us with your deliciousness and to all of the artists we met creating your own beautiful work. The harmony of emptiness and filling up, loss and replenishment… a mystery indeed. ❤️

Deep in another round of record making w @johnalagia and @thegrip  Ever grateful for the talented gems that lend their artistry and guidance to this process.  It has been stop starts for years, but we are back IN IT and the renewal to what I feel drawn to contribute is growing again.  I’m collaborating w many on this next batch of songs and the ride feels right.  So fortunate to have great friends that are up for a challenge and believe in what’s happening on this end. Thank you to all who understand my ins and outs, here sometimes and then not way of being right now. It is the ‘labor process’ as true as to how I will ever get to experience it. ❤️❤️❤️

Please think some loving thoughts for my friend Michael McCartney in Maui. He’s supported many of my artist friends and I far beyond just playing us on the radio and being our tour guide over many years. He is laughter and kindness and has a whole family of stray cats that he fed on his front lawn. If he’s at a shelter now I have no doubt he is lifting the spirits of all around him.  Sending you strength and love during this devastating and shocking time. Donate if you can and of course our hearts go out to all going through this. ❤️
❤️❤️❤️ thank you for the kind thoughts for my friend. He is very fortunately accounted for.  Sending love to all through this time.
It has been a long time coming, but this fall I will be headed back to Asia. Our China dates will begin the run.  More dates to be announced soon. Tix links on my website in bio ❤️💃🏻🥰

Super blue moon energy creation of ‘Galaxy’ yesterday with dream team @_s.a.n.d.y.b.e.l.l._ @jefflipstein and always @thegrip .  They say a record is a moment in time and I’m so glad we captured our bits last night as we did for this very special song.  Every track is forming with a an intuitive cast of people beyond dear to my heart.  The flow, generosity and guidance I am experiencing with each party that lends their talents is a gift of absolute abundance that is just joy.  There are no rules to this one, no traditional expectations, no maps other than what each day inspires.  The trust on every level is allowing the greatest leaps and I just feel we are going to land in a beautiful place. Sandy and Jeff - you need a production team name. Thank you @utopiabearsville .  Thank you to the future gems that wanna come join the party. We go on. ❤️❤️❤️
New shows announced for Hong Kong, Taipei and Seoul.  I am beyond the garden and beyond excited about this.  Info in bio. ❤️❤️❤️

So much fun @rhettmiller songwriting is magic camp! I only wish I had taken more pix. Congrats Rhett for slam dunking the first one - such a delight to watch you guide so beautifully and provide so much love and joy to an incredible mix of peeps.  I loved talking to everyone and am leaving truly inspired on a personal and artistic level. The gang’s signed poster will go by my piano to always remind a gal of the love and connection.  Forgive me for my Irish goodbye as I dive head first back into travel logistics, rehearsals and squirrel care.  So much love to you all ❤️❤️❤️❤️

These words came up when sitting with the past week.  May we shed our visions of separation from self and other. Hold light, compassion, love.  Create something better, bolder, connected again.  From the heart. Always from the heart.  Condemn and transmute hatred, targeting, threats, murder, war, on any and all, with little and large actions of its opposite.  Human on human on self on human.

4th show in a row tonight w 1 1/2hr signings after each and planes, trains and vans, but omg it’s a blast. I am beyond grateful for these loving fans. We are connecting across cultures, language, experience and sharing these precious moments of unity. Never before have I felt the power of live performance and music to act as a heart to heart connective force like this. Floored by the love. Thank you @connorfkennedy @willibtx and of course @thegrip for joining on this ride. ❤️❤️❤️
Pink. ❤️

Home. Processing the lovely, replenishing, electric and just truly special tour with all things that settle me in - feeding Lucky the squirrel (still here!), dressing down and enjoying my sisters and their company.  Today I drained the little pond and left a little water for my frog friend. Winterizing the garden, keeping the fire goin and getting ready to return to recording… every day is a treasure and each moment it’s own kind of thrill.  I call out ‘Lucky’ every morning and it’s taken on a deeper meaning with or without the nuts. Ha. ❤️

Back in it w @johnalagia @connorfkennedy @brandon__morrison @thegrip and Moshi the wonder cat that needs to be a part of it all. When I get asked ‘how much of your house to you ‘really’ use for work..I just laugh ❤️❤️❤️
